"Xi Jinping sends a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum - Xinhua News."
"Xinhua News, Beijing, December 11th: On December 11th, President Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum."
"President Xi Jinping pointed out that the world is currently undergoing an unprecedented great change of the century, global scientific and technological innovation has entered a densely active period, and the new round of technological revolution and industrial change has had a profound impact on the global economic structure."
"The Greater Bay Area of Guangdong, Hong Kong, and Macao should focus on the strategy of building an international center for scientific and technological innovation, strive to build a global highland of scientific and technological innovation, and promote the development of emerging industries."
"China is willing to work closely with scientists from all over the world and international scientific and technological organizations to strengthen international scientific and technological exchanges and cooperation, enhance research on major scientific issues, promote the common solution of scientific and technological issues, deepen cooperation on key scientific projects, and jointly promote the development of the world's scientific cause, so as to better benefit humanity."
"The 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum was opened on the same day in Guangzhou, Guangdong Province, with the theme "Exploring the Future, Sharing Science". It was sponsored by the People's Government of Guangdong Province."